.TH "intel_psr_wait_for_idle" 9 "intel_psr_wait_for_idle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_psr_wait_for_idle \- wait for PSR1 to idle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" intel_psr_wait_for_idle
.BI "(const struct intel_crtc_state *new_crtc_state "  ","
.BI "u32 *out_value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "new_crtc_state" 12
new CRTC state
.IP "out_value" 12
PSR status in case of failure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is expected to be called from \fBpipe_update_start\fP where it is
not expected to race with PSR enable or disable.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or -ETIMEOUT if PSR status does not idle.
